bilingual.source: A relatively modest intervention could have a big impact.
bilingual.target: 相对适度的干预可能会产生巨大的影响。

bilingual.source: When employees are properly compensated, employers' real estate savings will be modest.
bilingual.target: 当雇员得到适当的补偿时，雇主的房地产储蓄将是适度的。
那本书受到了适度的夸赞。

bilingual.source: They require a modest amount of exercise.
Tourism still making modest progress despite all that.
bilingual.target: 尽管如此，旅游业依然有适度的发展。

bilingual.source: But there was just a modest effect on other common teen problems.
bilingual.target: 但是对于其他常见的青少年问题只是有一个适度的影响。

bilingual.source: In principle a modest dose of controlled inflation might work wonders.
bilingual.target: 原则上，适度的可控性的通胀可能会产生奇效。

bilingual.source: All of this suggests the cost of Mr Snowden's revelations has been modest.
bilingual.target: 所有的一切都表明斯诺登事件的代价是适度的。

bilingual.source: The risk of a wage - price spiral, albeit a modest one, is not negligible.
bilingual.target: 工资 - 价格螺旋上升, 即使是一种适度的上升, 其风险也是不可小视的.

bilingual.source: The seemingly modest unemployment rate of 4.4% in February understates the pain.
bilingual.target: 二月份貌似适度的4.4%的失业率并没有如实地反映痛苦。

list.abstract: modest（英 [ˈmɒdɪst]，美 [ˈmɑːdɪst]），英语单词，作形容词为谦虚的；谦逊的；谦恭的。短语搭配有modest increase（适当增加）。例句为“You should remain modest when approaching perfection.（当你接近完美时，你应该保持谦虚。）” modest相关近义词有odest、inobtrusive，相关反义词有immodest。

yingyinNormal.en: We've actually begun to see some modest wage growth in recent months. But most folks still haven't seen a raise in over a decade.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实际上，我们在最近几个月，已经开始看到一些适度的工资增长。但大部分人仍然在十多年来没能见到工资地上涨。

yingyinNormal.en: Many of these organizations are modest in size but inspire me with the work they do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些组织有的规模并不算大，但他们所做的一切却常常鼓舞了我。

yingyinNormal.en: How do you know? Well, on your salary, it would have to be modest, and you spent all the money on that cottage, didn't you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么知道？凭你的工资，你不能过得太阔绰，而且你把钱都花在那间农舍上了吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Because she's shy! Bingley too, is modest and was persuaded she didn't feel strongly for him. Because you suggested it. I did it for his own good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是因为她害羞！彬格莱被说服了，她的感觉并不强列。是你说的。我这样做是为了他好。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't believe you did this. It's amazing! Oh, it's not a big deal. Just to be clear, it was a big deal. I was being modest. You got that, right? Loud and clear.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真不敢相信你做了这些。太棒了！没什么大不了的啦。怕你误会，这的确是有大不了。我刚才只是谦虚。你有听懂的吧？如雷贯耳。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: A relatively <highlight>modest</highlight> intervention could have a big impact.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相对适度的干预可能会产生巨大的影响。

examination_example.sentence: On a five to three vote, the Supreme Court knocked out much of Arizona's immigration law Monday — a <highlight>modest</highlight> policy victory for the Obama Administration.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 周一，最高法院以五比三的投票结果推翻了亚利桑那州的许多移民法——这是奥巴马政府在政策上的一次些许的胜利。

examination_example.sentence: Politicians have repeatedly "backloaded" public-sector pay deals, keeping the pay increases <highlight>modest</highlight> but adding to holidays and especially pensions that are already generous.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 政客们一再“偷偷提高”公共部门的工资待遇，虽然工资增长幅度不大，但假期增加了，尤其是增加了原来就已经非常高的养老金。

sense_info_list.en: marked by simplicity; having a humble opinion of yourself

examination_example.sentence: The court would be recklessly <highlight>modest</highlight> if it followed California's advice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果法院听从加州的建议，它将会不顾一切地保持谦虚。
